      <page>
        <exercise workspace="1in">
          <statement>
            <p>
              Prove the reduction formula
              <me>
                \int \cos^nx\,dx = \frac{1}{n} \cos^{n-1}x \sin x + \frac{n-1}{n}\int\cos^{n-2}x\,dx.
              </me>
            </p>
          </statement>

          <hint>
            <p>
              You are going to integrate <em>something</em> by parts.
              How can you break up <m>\cos^n x\,dx</m> into <m>u \,dv</m> that makes <m>dv</m> easily to integrate?
